A photorealistic aerial view of Sigiriya rock fortress in Sri Lanka at golden hour, the ancient lion rock rising dramatically from lush green jungle canopy, morning mist swirling around its base, tropical birds in flight, the surrounding landscape showing both serene beauty and subtle shadows creeping across the terrain, warm sunlight illuminating the weathered stone walls while darker clouds gather on the distant horizon, creating a striking contrast between paradise and underlying tension, shot with cinematic depth and rich natural colors.
